This paper discusses security weaknesses in remote user authentication schemes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with cryptographic protocols. Additionally, the paper discusses cyber security (cs.CY) as it involves the security of remote authentication systems. The paper also involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the vulnerabilities of proposed schemes. Finally, the paper involves distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it discusses the efficiency of the proposed schemes.
